  WateringDescription: Every 1-2 weeks
  TemperatureDegree: 0.65
  TemperatureDescription: "25 ~ 32\u2103"
  Tutorial:
  - Description: Before sowing seeds in a pot or hanging basket, ensure that the
      bottom of the pot has holes. This step is crucial to protect the seeds or prevent
      seedlings from rotting due to poor drainage. A common technique is to place
      some pumice, perlite, or gravel at the bottom of the pot, then add soil on
      top to improve drainage and aeration.
    ShortDescription: Use a shovel to scoop soil into the pot
  - Description: Generally, large-flowered plants need extra space to expand. We
      can leave morning glory seeds on the surface rather than burying them deep
      into the soil.
    ShortDescription: Place the morning glory seeds on the soil surface
  - Description: Morning glories are climbing plants, which means they will need
      a trellis to twine around and grow upwards. Typically, a long stick inserted
      into the soil is sufficient. Morning glory seeds need light to germinate, so
      you can sow them in a sunny location.
    ShortDescription: Place the trellis in the flower pot
